---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { site } from '../config/site';
import '../styles/legal.css';

const lastUpdated = 'June 5, 2026';
---

<Base
  title="Terms of Use | Freedom with AI"
  description="The terms that govern your use of the Freedom with AI website."
>
  <Nav />
  <main id="main-content" class="container legal-page">
    <div class="legal-page__inner">
      <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
      <p class="legal-page__updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <p class="legal-page__lede">
        These Terms of Use (&ldquo;Terms&rdquo;) govern your use of the
        <strong>freedomwith.ai</strong> website operated by {site.brand}
        (&ldquo;we,&rdquo; &ldquo;us,&rdquo; or &ldquo;our&rdquo;). By using the site, you
        agree to these Terms. If you do not agree, please do not use the site.
      </p>

      <h2>Scope</h2>
      <p>
        These Terms apply to this website only. Our product,
        <a href={site.faibuddyUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">faibuddy</a>,
        and any advisory engagement are governed by their own separate agreements.
      </p>

      <h2>Use of the site</h2>
      <p>You agree to use the site lawfully and not to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Disrupt, damage, or attempt to gain unauthorized access to the site or its systems.</li>
        <li>Copy, scrape, or reuse our content beyond what these Terms allow.</li>
        <li>Use the site to send spam or to misrepresent your identity.</li>
        <li>Infringe the rights of others or violate any applicable law.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
      <p>
        The site and its content&mdash;including text, design, graphics, logos, and
        videos&mdash;are owned by {site.brand} or our licensors and are protected by
        intellectual property laws. You may view and share our content for personal,
        non-commercial purposes with attribution. Any other use requires our prior written
        permission.
      </p>

      <h2>Inquiries and advisory</h2>
      <p>
        Contacting us or applying to work with us does not create a client relationship or
        any obligation on either side. Advisory engagements are selective and begin only
        under a separate written agreement. Nothing on this site is a promise or guarantee
        of any particular outcome or result.
      </p>

      <h2>No professional advice</h2>
      <p>
        Content on this site is provided for general informational and educational purposes.
        It is not legal, financial, tax, investment, or other professional advice, and it is
        not a substitute for advice tailored to your situation. You are responsible for your
        own decisions.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-party links</h2>
      <p>
        The site links to third-party services such as faibuddy, YouTube, X, and LinkedIn.
        We do not control and are not responsible for the content, policies, or practices of
        those services. Accessing them is at your own risk and subject to their terms.
      </p>

      <h2>Disclaimers</h2>
      <p>
        The site is provided &ldquo;as is&rdquo; and &ldquo;as available,&rdquo; without
        warranties of any kind, whether express or implied, including fitness for a
        particular purpose and non-infringement. We do not warrant that the site will be
        uninterrupted, error-free, or secure.
      </p>

      <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the fullest extent permitted by law, {site.brand} will not be liable for any
        indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, or any loss of
        profits, data, or goodwill, arising from your use of the site.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these Terms from time to time. Changes take effect when posted, and we
        will revise the &ldquo;Last updated&rdquo; date above. Your continued use of the site
        means you accept the updated Terms.
      </p>

      <h2>Governing law</h2>
      <p>
        These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of California, United States,
        without regard to its conflict-of-laws rules, and you agree to the exclusive
        jurisdiction of the courts located there.
      </p>

      <div class="legal-page__contact">
        <h2>Contact us</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about these Terms? Reach us through our
          <a href="/contact"> contact page</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Base>
